cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is about the robustness of deep classifiers against adversarial examples, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the security aspect of adversarial examples, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a theoretical framework based on topology, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
